{{Infobox Theatre |name = Azerbaijan State Theatre of Musical Comedy |image = Azerbaijan State Theatre of Musical Comedy 12.JPG |caption = |address = Z. Aliyeva St. 8 |city = Baku Azerbaijan |pushpin_map= |latitude = |longitude = |architect = |owner = |operator = |capacity = |type = |opened = {{Start date|1982|||df=y}} |rebuilt = |closed = |othernames = |production = |publictransit = |website = http://musiqiliteatr.az }} '''Azerbaijan State Theatre of Musical Comedy''' ({{lang-az|Azərbaycan Dövlət Musiqili Komediya Teatrı}}) – is one of the leading musical theatres of [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{Cite news | title = Азербайджанский Театр Музыкальной Комедии | url=http://www.all-pages.com/city_info/3/29/92/4679.html | publisher= | date= | accessdate = }}</ref>
==History== The premiere of ''Husband and wife'', a musical comedy written by [[Uzeyir Hajibeyov]] in 1909, was held on May 24, 1910 in the building of the Nikitin brothers’ circus, in [[Baku]]. This production laid the foundation of Azerbaijan State Theatre of Musical Comedy. By 1938, musical comedies were displayed on the stage of [[Azerbaijan State Academic Opera and Ballet Theater]]. In 1938, an independent theatre of musical comedy (with [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]] and [[Russian language|Russian]] departments), which acquired official status of "Azerbaijan State Theatre of Musical Comedy" in September of the same year, was organized. In 1939, the first Azerbaijani and [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] musical comedies such as ''Bride for 5 manats'' ([[Said Rustamov|S.Rustamov]]), ''Husband and wife'',''The married bachelor'', (later ''Whose wedding?'') (A.Mashadibeyov) and ''Roza'' (S.Hajibeyov) were staged. Comedies such as ''[[The Blue Mazurka|Blue mazurka]]'' ([[Franz Lehár]]), ''Arshin mal alan'' (U.Hajibeyov), ''[[Die Zirkusprinzessin|The Circus Princess]] '' ([[Emmerich Kálmán|Imre Kálmán]]), ''Wedding in Malinovka'' (B.Aleksandrov) and others were staged by the Russian department of the theatre.<ref>{{Cite news | title = Азербайджанский Государственный Театр Музыкальной Комедии | url=http://www.azerbaijans.com/content_207_ru.html | publisher=azerbaijans.com | date= | accessdate = }}</ref>
From the 1940s onwards, the theatre took a significant place in cultural life of Azerbaijan.
The absence of a building for the theatre in the period 1988-1992, coupled with socio-political events in the new Republic, affected the creative activity of the theatre’s collective. However the theatre then entered into a new stage of its development, in a new building. Amongst the pieces presented were: ''[[If Not That One, Then This One]], Konul, Love on the stage, Goodbye!, Everyone has his own star'', and others.<ref>{{Cite news | title = Азербайджанский Государственный театр музыкальной комедии им.Шихали Курбанова | url=http://www.ourbaku.com/index.php5/%D0%90%D0%B7%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B1%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B4%D0%B6%D0%B0%D0%BD%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9_%D0%93%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%83%D0%B4%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B2%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D1%8B%D0%B9_%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%B0%D1%82%D1%80_%D0%BC%D1%83%D0%B7%D1%8B%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%BB%D1%8C%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B9_%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%B8%D0%B8_%D0%B8%D0%BC.%D0%A8%D0%B8%D1%85%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B8_%D0%9A%D1%83%D1%80%D0%B1%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B0 | publisher=ourbaku.com | date= | accessdate = }}</ref>
