{{infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Only When I Larf | title_orig = | translator = | image = Image:OnlyWhenILarf.jpg | caption = First edition cover | author = [[Len Deighton]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | series = | genre = Comic [[thriller novel]] | publisher = [[Sphere Books]] | release_date = 1968 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print ([[Paperback]]) | pages = | isbn = 0-7221-2986-6 | oclc = 255886426 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
[[Len Deighton]]'s '''''Only When I Larf''''' is a late 1960s British comic thriller describing the activities of a team of three [[confidence trick]]sters led by Silas Lowther (late 40s), his girlfriend Liz Mason (late 20s) and wannabe apprentice and Liz-worshipper Bob (early 20s). It was published in 1968 by [[Michael Joseph (publisher)|Michael Joseph]] and in paperback by [[Sphere Books|Sphere]]. It is currently (2012) printed by Harper in the UK.
The novel interleaves [[first-person narrative]]s from Bob (76 pages in 7 chapters), Liz (78 pages in 6 chapters) and Silas (88 pages in 5 chapters). Their increasingly contradictory descriptions of shared experiences contribute to the humour. This [[Unreliable narrator|unreliable narration]] adds to the atmosphere around deceiving "the marks", but the characters' different perspectives on their mutual relationship (interspersed with Silas's day-dreams of a dishonourable wartime incident) look more like self-deception and often add a poignant note. The title is explained in a variety of unlikely anecdotes where in each case a critically injured third party bravely replies this when asked "Does it hurt?"
==Adaptations== A film adaptation of ''[[Only When I Larf (film)|Only When I Larf]]'', directed by [[Basil Dearden]],<ref name=V>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/1967/film/reviews/only-when-i-larf-1200421591/ |title=Only When I Larf |publisher=Variety |date=1967-12-31 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> was released in 1968 starring [[Richard Attenborough]] as Silas, [[David Hemmings]] as Bob and [[Alexandra Stewart]] as Liz and has been well reviewed,<ref>[http://www.channel4.com/film/reviews/film.jsp?id=106764 Channel4.com]</ref><ref>[[Vincent Canby]]. [https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9E0CE7D71530E034BC4C51DFB6678383679EDE ''The New York Times'']. Retrieved 28 April 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117793740.html?categoryid=31&cs=1&p=0 ''Variety'']. Retrieved 28 April 2013.</ref> though some feel it is "a plodding adaptation" of the original novel.<ref>[http://www.timeout.com/film/newyork/reviews/66125/only-when-i-larf.html ''Time Out'']. Retrieved 28 April 2013.</ref>
